@node "Overview" "Overview"
@next "Installation"
@prev "Main"

@{b}rpl@{ub} is a search and replace tool for the Amiga.
I wrote this piece of software because I have many times
needed one, but I've never bothered to look for one... :)

The requirements for running rpl are:

 Ę Amiga computer :)
 Ę AmigaOS 1.2 (?)
 Ę 68020

The 68020 is necessary because I compiled it that way,
but if you REALLY need a 68000-version, contact me...

@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"
@next "Usage"
@prev "Overview"

Not much to say here really.

Ę Copy the binary to your C: assign.

@endnode

@node "Usage" "Using rpl"
@next "Options"
@prev "Installation"

rpl is designed to be run from CLI.
I might - if I need it - add some sort of GUI...

To convert a file, run the command @{b}rpl@{ub} with the @{"options" link "Options" 0}
you find appropriate, don't forget the target- and
destinationfiles.

@endnode

@node "Options" "Options"
@next "License"
@prev "Usage"

CLI Options:


  -[cdho] [input] [output]

  -c

    Character mode.
    @{b}No strings!@{ub}

  -d

    Decimal mode.

  -h

    Hexadecimal mode.

  -o

    Octal mode.

  input

    The name of the file to be read.

  output

    The new file, which is to be created. If the specified file
    exists it will be owerwritten.

@endnode

